From: DMP-ART Design System refresh
Subject: [PATCH] Cyan-shifted palette + gold dark-mode logo

Two changes to align with the new design tokens:

  1. CSS variables — light + dark theme palettes shifted from pure
     blue toward a teal/cyan undertone (hue ~+12° toward green).
     Polish diacritics font support unchanged (Plus Jakarta Sans
     already covers Latin Extended-A in static/css/style.css).

  2. New asset static/images/dmp-art-logo-main-dark-gold.png — a
     variant of the dark logo where the "DMP" lettering is gold
     (#e5ad1a) instead of light grey, for better punch on dark UI.

Apply with:    git apply design-system-refresh.patch
              (then copy the PNG separately — git apply skips binaries)

==============================================================
diff --git a/static/css/style.css b/static/css/style.css
--- a/static/css/style.css
+++ b/static/css/style.css
@@ -16,11 +16,11 @@
 }

